## Steps

### step 1
id: go-to-custom-rules
instruction: Go to Scrub Rules (sidebar > Altair Intelligence > Scrub Rules) and click the "Custom Rules" tab.
success_criteria: The Custom Rules tab is active. You can see a yellow-highlighted "Proposed Rules" section at the top if any exist.
anchor: "Custom Rules"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Scrub Rules link is in the sidebar. Click the Custom Rules tab once on the page.

### step 2
id: read-proposed-rule
instruction: Click on a proposed rule card to expand it and read: rule type (e.g., Modifier Requirement), which procedure or diagnosis codes it affects, which payer it applies to (or "All Payers"), severity level, and how many times this pattern was detected.
success_criteria: You understand what Altair is proposing and why.
anchor: "proposed rule card"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Proposed rules are in a yellow section at the top of the Custom Rules list. Click one to expand it.

### step 3
id: decide-on-rule
instruction: Decide whether to activate or reject the rule. Click "Accept" if it's a valid pattern worth enforcing on future claims. Click "Reject" if it's not applicable to your practice.
success_criteria: You have clicked either Accept or Reject.
anchor: "Accept"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Accept and Reject buttons are on the proposed rule card.

### step 4
id: confirm
instruction: Confirm your action if prompted.
success_criteria: If accepted: the rule moves to the active custom rules list and will now catch matching claims. If rejected: the proposed rule disappears.
anchor: "Confirm"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click the confirmation button if a dialog appears.

## Completion Message
done. if you activated it, this rule will now catch future claims matching that pattern before they go to the payer — preventing that denial from recurring. altair continues learning and will propose new rules as new patterns emerge.

